---

Adjust rack to top position (top and middle positions for 4 servings) and preheat #oven{} to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Halve, peel, and cut @red onion{1} into ½-inch-thick wedges; mince a few wedges until you have 2 TBSP (4 TBSP for 4). Peel and mince or grate @garlic{1%clove}.

> Reserve some garlic for the rice and some for the white sauce.

Drain and rinse @chickpeas{13.4%ounce can}; dry thoroughly with #paper towels{}. Roughly chop @cilantro{1/4%ounce}. Zest and quarter @lemon{1}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{2%tsp} in a small #pot{} (use a medium pot for 4 servings) over medium-high heat. Add minced onion, half the garlic, half the @shawarma spice blend{1%tbsp}, and a pinch of @salt{}. Cook, stirring, ~{1%minute}.

Stir in @basmati rice{1/2%cup}, 3/4 cup water (1 1/2 cups for 4), @veggie stock concentrate{1}, and a big pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce heat to low. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to use in step 5.

Meanwhile, toss onion wedges, @grape tomatoes{4%ounce}, and chickpeas on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @olive oil{2%tsp}, remaining Shawarma Spice, @pepper{}, and a few pinches of @salt{}.

> For 4 servings, divide everything between 2 baking sheets; roast on top and middle racks, tossing veggies and swapping rack positions halfway through roasting.

Roast on top rack, tossing halfway through, until veggies are tender and lightly charred and chickpeas are crispy, ~{18-20%minutes}. (It's natural for chickpeas to pop a bit while roasting.)

While everything roasts, pat @salmon{10%ounce} dry with paper towels and season all over with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Once veggies have roasted ~{10%minutes}, carefully push to one side and add salmon, skin sides down, to same baking sheet. Roast until salmon is cooked through, ~{8-10%minutes} more.

Meanwhile, in a small #bowl{}, combine @sour cream{4%tablespoon} and remaining garlic to taste. Season with @salt{}. Stir in water 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in half the cilantro and @butter{1/2%tablespoon} (1 TBSP for 4 servings). Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Once veggies and chickpeas are done, remove from oven and toss with lemon zest.

Divide rice between shallow #bowls{}. Top with veggies and chickpeas. Drizzle with garlicky white sauce and @hot sauce{1%tsp} to taste. Sprinkle with remaining cilantro. Top with lemon juice to taste; serve with any remaining lemon wedges on the side.

Serve salmon atop rice.